<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Tutorial</title>
    <style>
        p{
            color: darkblue;
            background-color: greenyellow;
        }
    </style>
    <!-- the style is used in the head of the plate to inlcude Internal CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css1tut10.css">
    <!-- link is used to patch external CSS into html  -->
</head>
<body>
    <h3>This is CSS Tutorial</h3>
    <p>This Tutorial will teach you everything you need to know about HTML/CSS </p>
    <p>There are 3 types of CSS</p>
    <p style="color: rgb(123, 8, 238); background-color: cyan;">First is Inline CSS</p>
     <!-- This is how we put a css property in a specifc line -->
    <p>Second is Internal CSS</p>
    <!-- Internal CSS is added by using style keyword in head of html  -->
    <p>And the Third one is External CSS</p>
    <!-- External CSS is added by the link keyword  -->
    <!-- Order of priority of the css types is 
     Inline > External > Internal  -->
</body>
</html>
